NOVAK is provided freely for election oversight systems. Any state or federal
voting authority may use the NOVAK Protocol to ensure that the rules governing
ballot processing, tabulation, and auditing are provably executed as written —
transparently, deterministically, and without reliance on institutional trust.

The NOVAK Protocol may be used at no cost by:

• All Federal agencies of the United States Government, EXCEPT:
  – The United States Department of War (historical; now Department of Defense)
